PR Title:
Product Edit Flow — Group 2 (Pricing & Inventory)
PR Description:
## Overview
Implements the Product Edit Flow for Group 2 — Pricing & Inventory tabs — 
within the Codem Shopify embedded app.

## Route
`/app/products/:handle/edit`

## Tabs
- **Tab A: Pricing** — Price, compare-at price, cost per item, taxable, tax code, currency
- **Tab B: Inventory** — Track quantity, quantity per location, allow oversell, SKU, barcode (lazy-loaded)

## Diff Strategy
On save, the form submits both current values and original values (prefixed `orig_`).
The action computes a diff before firing any mutations:
- If nothing changed → zero mutations fire (no-op save)
- If pricing fields changed → `productVariantsBulkUpdate` fires
- If cost per item changed → `inventoryItemUpdate` fires
- If inventory quantity changed → `inventoryAdjustQuantities` fires
- If oversell policy changed → `productVariantsBulkUpdate` fires
- If SKU changed → `productVariantsBulkUpdate` (with inventoryItem.sku) fires
- If barcode changed → `productVariantsBulkUpdate` fires
- If tracked changed → `inventoryItemUpdate` fires
- If both pricing and inventory changed → all relevant mutations fire in one submission

## Global Save / Discard
- Persistent header bar with Save and Discard buttons outside tab content
- Shared state via `useReducer` — switching tabs never resets unsaved edits
- Global `isDirty` flag derived by diffing combined form state against original values
- Save disabled when `isDirty` is false
- Discard reverts entire combined form state to original loader values

## Lazy Loading
Tab B (Inventory) is never loaded in the initial loader response.
It is fetched via `useFetcher` only when the merchant clicks the Inventory tab for the first time.

## Admin Extension
Reads product ID from extension context → resolves handle via GraphQL → 
navigates to edit page → closes modal immediately.
`APP_HANDLE` defined in centralised `config.js`.

## Error Messages
All 10 deterministic error messages (E-01 to E-10) implemented verbatim per spec.
